As to the whole 'but we're clan' answers from people. It'd be funny if I could say that I might have had a hand in that, as honestly, outside of _my_ team, I refuse to buff Omnis. I mean, it's just not something I need to do, and repeatedly, repeatedly I've sent /tells to Omnis that just say &quot;Sorry man, I don't buff Omnis outside of missions.&quot; And that usually shuts people up. Or makes them start offering money, which is funny, because I hardly need money anymore.<br>
<br>
So... Ahh... Yeah. Think about the buffs you get from people, and the buffs you might want to get from random people that you meet on the street. Also, remember that we're coming up on, or have already engaged in war. Do you, or do you not want to give your side a helping hand? That's why I'll drop buffs on clanners. 'Cause I figure one of 'em will have my back someday.<br>
